id-19. your healthcare \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tprovider can recommend additional steps you may be able to take \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tto protect yourself.", " \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tthere isn't yet specific information about the risk of serious \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tillness from covid-19 in people with hiv. until more is known, \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tthe ", "what \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdo i do if i've tested positive for covid-19?", "in the u.s., covid-19 can only be confirmed with a \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tlaboratory test. outside of the u.s., sometimes covid-19 is \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tdiagnosed based on symptoms only. if you've been diagnosed with \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tcovid-19, you should follow your healthcare provider's \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tinstructions very closely, avoid public places and wear a mask \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tif you have to be around other people. those caring directly for \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tyou should wear masks when they are with you as well. you will \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tneed to practice self-isolation.", "in general, the larger the gathering, the more \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\topportunities there are for person-to-person contact and \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttherefore greater risk of spreading covid-19 virus. a covid-19 \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\toutbreak could last a long time in your community. depending on \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tthe severity of the outbreak, public health officials may \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\trecommend specific actions, such as closing schools and public \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tlocations, in order to help keep people healthy, reduce \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\texposures to covid-19 and slow the spread of the disease. these \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tmitigation strategies are particularly important in order to \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tslow the transmission of disease in order to protect:", "why is getting a flu shot important during \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tcovid-19?", " \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\taccording to the cdc, getting the flu shot each year is the best \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tway to help protect against the flu. during the pandemic, \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tgetting the flu shot may be even more important. receivin