{"website": "https://www.walgreens.com/topic/promotion/covid-vaccine.jsp", "retailer": "walgreens", "text": ["covid-19 vaccine: faqs & distribution information | walgreens", "covid-19 vaccine: faqs & distribution information | walgreens", "covid-19 vaccine update:", "covid-19 vaccine", "covid-19 vaccine", "how effective is the covid-19 vaccine? who will get it first? how does a vaccine trial work? our expert pharmacists and a member of the fda\u2019s vaccine advisory committee weigh in.", "dr. paul offit joins us to discuss the safety of the covid-19 vaccines and more.", "dr. leana wen discusses vaccine developments and how to keep your family covid-free this holiday.", "who is eligible for a covid-19 vaccination?", "per cdc guidance, covid-19 vaccinations are currently only available to:", "browse additional covid-19 resources to help you stay informed", "explore how walgreens is helping you and your family through covid-19.", "covid-19 testing is now available at walgreens.", "stay up to date on our response to the coronavirus pandemic.", "are covid-19 vaccines available?", " \t\t\t\t\tthe fda has granted emergency use authorization for the covid-19 vaccine developed by pfizer and biontech. this vaccine will be available to select eligible populations including healthcare workers and residents of long-term care facilities. covid-19 vaccines are anticipated to be available to the general population sometime in 2021. \t\t\t\t  ", "who is eligible to get a covid-19 vaccine?", " \t\t\t\t   the cdc has outlined a three-phased approach for the administration of covid-19 vaccines. the federal government, working with the states, are prioritizing high-risk populations for initial distribution, with plans to expand access to the general population based on availability of adequate supply of covid-19 vaccines. we anticipate vaccines will be available for the general population through our more than 9,000 stores sometime in 2021. \t\t\t\t  ", "who can get a covid-19 vaccine first?", " \t\t\t\t  healthcare workers, residents of long-term care facilities and select populations have been deemed eligible for the covid-19 vaccine by the cdc. when vaccines are more widely available, there will be increased access to the broader population.   \t\t\t\t  ", "can i get a covid-19 vaccine at walgreens?", "what safety measures will walgreens be taking when administering covid-19 vaccines?", " \t\t\t\t  walgreens knows safety is of utmost importance to customers during the covid-19 pandemic. in accordance with the cdc, we\u2019re taking health and safety measures including physical distancing and personal protective equipment in our stores and off-site clinics. walgreens will continue to meet or exceed cdc guidelines for immunizations to promote the health and wellbeing of our team members and customers.     \t\t\t\t  ", "are covid-19 vaccines safe?", " \t\t\t\t  vaccines have played an important role in protecting the health and safety of communities and nations throughout history. as a critical resource for care in our communities, walgreens will remain focused on providing safe and convenient access to covid-19 vaccines. ", "how does the covid-19 vaccine work?", " \t\t\t\t  three types of covid-19 vaccines are currently or soon will be undergoing clinical trials in the united states: mrna, protein subunit and vector. each uses different technologies that recognize and protect us from covid-19. ", "how many shots of covid-19 vaccine are required?", "is my covid-19 vaccine at walgreens free?", "*walgreens is following cdc guidelines to provide safe access to covid-19 vaccines. vaccines will be subject to availability. state-, age- and health- related restrictions may apply."]}
