are two cases of covid-19 in different communities and how cloth face coverings or face masks and social distancing may have impacted their spread.", "case 1: unmasked choir practice results in 87% spread after reported covid-19 infection", "on march 10, 2020\u2014before masks were recommended by the cdc\u2014a group of 61 singers met for choir practice in mount vernon, washington, including someone who had been fighting cold-like symptoms for a few days. they sang close together and shared snacks after practice without wearing masks. the sick person later tested positive for covid-19\u2014 and within two days of the practice, six total members of the choir had developed a fever. ultimately, 53 members of the choir became ill with covid-19, and three of them were hospitalized and two of them died.", "case 2: masked hair salon results in 0% spread after reported covid-19 infections", "wearing cloth face coverings or face masks may have been the reason nearly 140 people were spared covid-19 infection at a hair salon in missouri. in may, dozens of people interacted with two hair stylists who confirmed to have been working while infected with covid-19. but none of the other people ended up showing symptoms of the disease.", "just because your city or state may have started to reopen, this doesn't mean it's safe to ignore precautions or that cases are decreasing. in order to slow the spread of covid-19, the cdc urges we move forward together by ", "what type of face covering should i wear to protect from covid-19?", "of covid-19", "contact your health care provider if you develop symptoms of covid-19."]}
